<Primary>
<PrimaryPrelims>
<Title><?start-line?>A
<?new-line?>Bill

<?new-line?>To
</Title>
<Number /><LongTitle><?start-line?><Para>
<Text>Require that claims by employees alleging sexual impropriety be limited to <?new-line?>cases where the alleged misconduct is contrary to the criminal law and has <?new-line?>been reported to the police.<DateOfEnactment><DateText /></DateOfEnactment>
</Text>
</Para>
</LongTitle>
<DateOfEnactment><DateText /></DateOfEnactment>
<PrimaryPreamble>
<EnactingText>
<Para>
<Text>B<SmallCaps>e it enacted</SmallCaps> by the Queen’s most Excellent Majesty, by and with the advice and <?new-line?>consent of the Lords Spiritual and Temporal, and Commons, in this present <?new-line?>Parliament assembled, and by the authority of the same, as follows:—</Text>
</Para>
</EnactingText>
</PrimaryPreamble>
</PrimaryPrelims>
<Body NumberFormat="default">
<P1group id="p00003">
<Title><?start-line?>Allegations of sexual impropriety</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>No employee shall make an allegation of sexual impropriety against an <?new-line?>employer or a fellow employee as part of any proceedings before an <?new-line?>employment tribunal, unless that allegation has been referred by way of <?new-line?>complaint to the police prior to the commencement of such proceedings.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>For the purposes of this act “allegations of sexual impropriety” shall include <?new-line?>any allegation of sexual harassment or other sexual conduct which, if proved, <?new-line?>would amount to conduct contrary to the criminal law.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
<P1group id="p00004">
<Title><?start-line?>Short title and commencement</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act may be cited as the Sexual Impropriety in Employment Act 2013.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act comes into force at the end of the period of two months beginning <?new-line?>with the day on which this Act is passed.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
